Operatives of the Delta State Police Command’s Anti-Cult Unit have arrested a forty-eight-year-old suspect, Suleiman Musa and recovered five hundred and forty {540} rounds of live cartridges, three {03} Elepac Generators, one solar light, one {01} singer sewing machine, two {02} television sets and one {01} Lifan motorcycle all suspected to have been stolen. The arrest came following a raid of a criminal hideout in an uncompleted building along Mariam Babangida way opposite North-West filling Station Asaba, Delta State. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. According to the Police Image maker,” Investigation is ongoing.”